  "prompt": "Am I supposed to buy iPhone 6s Plus or I should wait for iPhone 7?",
  "response": "As of my last update, the iPhone 6s Plus and iPhone 7 have both been released and are considered older models now, with newer models available. Here are some points to consider if you are deciding between these two models:\n\n**iPhone 6s Plus:**\n- Released in September 2015.\n- Features a 5.5-inch Retina display.\n- Generally available at a lower price point compared to newer models.\n- Still supports popular apps and features, but software updates may be limited soon.\n\n**iPhone 7:**\n- Released in September 2016.\n- Includes improvements over the 6s Plus, such as a better camera, water resistance, and the A10 Fusion chip for better performance.\n- Removes the headphone jack, which may or may not be a significant factor for you.\n- Likely to receive iOS updates for a little longer than the iPhone 6s Plus.\n\n**Considerations:**\n- **Budget**: The iPhone 6s Plus might be more affordable than the iPhone 7, especially on the second-hand market.\n- **Performance and Features**: If you want slightly better performance and features, the iPhone 7 would be more beneficial.\n- **Latest Models**: Consider newer models like the iPhone SE (2020) or any newer versions if your budget allows, as they offer more features, support, and longevity with software updates.\n\nUltimately, if you\u2019re choosing solely between these two and want to stretch the functionality for a bit longer, the iPhone 7 would be the better choice. Otherwise, evaluating newer models might be worthwhile for more extended software support and better technology.",
